<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16579] Concurrent backup / restore support</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16579</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently we take exclusive lock on hbase:backup table in backup / restore procedures.&lt;br/&gt;
There is only one backup or restore operation which can run at given time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should consider using shared lock on hbase:backup table in the procedures so that concurrent backup / restore operations can proceed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The concurrency is useful when table sets don&apos;t overlap.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We may devise other mechanism(s) when there is overlap among the table sets.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
